## **ğŸ“Œ 5. Sum of Factors**
If **N = pâ¿ Ã— qáµ Ã— ráµ**, then:
```math
Sum = \frac{p^{(n+1)} - 1}{p - 1} \times \frac{q^{(m+1)} - 1}{q - 1} \times \frac{r^{(k+1)} - 1}{r - 1}
```

**Example:** Find sum of factors of **12**
```math
12 = 2Â² Ã— 3Â¹
```
```math
Sum = \frac{2Â³ - 1}{2 - 1} Ã— \frac{3Â² - 1}{3 - 1} = \frac{8 - 1}{1} Ã— \frac{9 - 1}{2} = 7 Ã— 4 = 28
```

